# Ledgerium AI — Event Schema Overview

## Purpose

This document defines the Event Schema, the foundational data model used to represent all recorded user behavior within Ledgerium AI.

It ensures that:
- all captured behavior is structured consistently
- events are privacy-safe by design
- downstream systems can deterministically reconstruct workflows

---

## Scope

This document covers:
- the structure of an event
- required and optional fields
- data normalization rules
- privacy constraints at the schema level
- relationships between events and sessions

This document does NOT cover:
- how events are captured (event-capture-spec.md)
- how events are processed into workflows (deterministic-process-engine.md)
- how events are visualized (UI specs)

---

