## Core Principle

> The schema captures structure, not content.

Events must contain:
- what happened
- where it happened
- when it happened
- what changed (if known)

Events must NOT contain:
- user-generated content
- sensitive data
- raw text inputs

---

## Event Definition

An Event is:

> A normalized, privacy-safe record of a single user action, system transition, or contextual change within a workflow.

---

## Event Characteristics

All events must be:

- **atomic** — represent a single meaningful occurrence
- **timestamped** — include precise timing
- **ordered** — part of a sequence
- **contextualized** — include environment metadata
- **sanitized** — free of sensitive content
- **deterministic** — consistently structured

